  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps</p><p>Wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1-1622807640336-1637684338897-x200.jpeg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1-1622807640336-1637684338897-x400.jpeg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1-1622807640336-1637684338897-x700.jpeg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1-1622807640336-1637684338897-x1000.jpeg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1-1622807640336-1637684338897-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge and open the packet to let it breathe before cooking and boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Combine the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>vinaigrette</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-2-1637684423211-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-2-1637684423211-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-2-1637684423211-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-2-1637684423211-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-2-1637684423211-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the pan is hot, add the<strong> diced chicken</strong> and cook for 2-3 min and then add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span>of <strong>flour</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-3-1637684447443-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-3-1637684447443-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-3-1637684447443-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-3-1637684447443-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-3-1637684447443-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>mustard stock</strong></p><p>Crumble the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into the pan and cook for a further 2 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-4-1637684476208-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-4-1637684476208-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-4-1637684476208-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-4-1637684476208-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723.-step-4-1637684476208-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> Chinese rice wine,</strong> <strong>mustard</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and the <strong>single soya </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat for a final 3 min or until the chicken is cooked through</p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>if needed – this is your <strong>dairy-free chicken & mushroom fricassée</strong></p><p>Note: Please make sure you cook your chicken thoroughly (until there’s no pink meat and it’s piping hot!) as cooking equipment varies</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723-v2-Step-5-1637684529748-x200.jpeg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723-v2-Step-5-1637684529748-x400.jpeg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723-v2-Step-5-1637684529748-x700.jpeg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723-v2-Step-5-1637684529748-x1000.jpeg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1723-v2-Step-5-1637684529748-x1500.jpeg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, squeeze the pouch<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> of<strong> steamed brown rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>baby leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p><p>Chop the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
